{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place fresh coriander into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place a deep bowl onto mixing bowl lid, insert simmering basket into it. Weigh in rice and 500 g water and set aside. Cut the tops of the peppers and reserve for later use, remove the seeds, place in a baking dish and set aside.","Place onions, garlic, 30 g oil, cumin, Arabic spice mix and cinnamon into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile preheat oven to 200ºC.","Add tomato purée, tomatoes, sugar, chili peppers, 1 tsp vegetable paste, salt and pepper into mixing bowl  and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add 250 g water and drained rice from simmering basket into mixing bowl and cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer rice mixture in a bowl, add shrimps, lemon juice, and reserved chopped coriander and mix gently. Without pressing the mixture, fill peppers up to ¾ with shrimp mixture, then replace cut-off top on each pepper and place back into ovenproof dish and set aside.","Place remaining 250 g water, 1 tsp vegetable stock paste, 10 g olive oil into mixing bowl and warm it <b>4 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>.  Transfer into ovenproof baking dish with stuffed peppers (liquid should be enough to cover up to 1 cm of the base of the baking dish). Cover with a sheet of aluminium foil and bake for 40-50 minutes (200°C). Remove cover and bake for additional 10 minutes. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["10 sprigs fresh coriander, roughly chopped","250 g Egyptian rice","1000 g water","10 - 12 peppers, mixed, medium-sized","200 g onions, cut into quarters","3 garlic cloves","40 g olive oil","1 tsp ground cumin","1 tsp Arabian spice mix","1 tsp ground cinnamon","1 tbsp tomato purée (concentrated)","300 g ripe tomatoes, cut into quarters","1 tsp sugar","2 small green chillies","2 tsp vegetable stock paste, homemade","1 tsp salt","1 pinch freshly ground black pepper","400 g raw shrimps, peeled, deveined","30 g lemon juice"]}],"id":"r168160","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-J6HAzbKLBwY\/XZQu1xKQQGI\/AAAAAAAAcXs\/J65efzWdRGAfox2LLOVWkjRAMiQmncmzwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_7M4Q9jVKUeJ3JrMj.png","title":"Shrimp stuffed bell peppers","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"16.5 g","fat":"8.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"51.5 g","calories":"2079 kJ \/ 346 kcal"},"usefulItems":"deep bowl, aluminium foil, baking dish, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Serve with Yoghurt and cucumber salad."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 25m","6 portions"]}